The paper deals with sparse recovery of signals defined over a graph, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. However, the use of incidence matrices and the focus on graph properties suggest that the paper is most likely to be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the study of cycles in graphs, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the use of specialized recovery algorithms and sparsity properties suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
